You can certainly make up scenarios where mech's make some sense, they're not too unrealistic in space combat (Gundam, Knights of Sidonia), small mechs for law enforcement applications make some sense (Patlabor, Appleseed), and if you can make up some bullshit biotech then it makes more sense to build a mech than a tank or a plane (Dunbine, Evangelion), but fundamentally they're just not realistic so why not throw caution to the wind and make something like Gurren Lagann or Diebuster?
